- '2022-2023 season' refers to a specific time period in the football calendar;
- 'league_id = 1' refers to a particular league in the database;
- 'average goals scored' is calculated by dividing the total goals scored by the number of matches played;
- 'shining stars' is a metaphorical expression for teams that performed exceptionally well;
- 'magical threshold of 1.5 goals per match' refers to the condition where the average goals scored by a team must be greater than 1.5.

- "best performance" refers to a combination of high average points and a high number of wins;
- "more than 50 points and more than 5 wins" are the initial conditions to filter out less relevant records;
- "average points greater than 60 and at least one season with more than 10 wins" are the final conditions to ensure the selected teams and seasons are top performers.

- "Best overall performance" is determined by the sum of the team's points and the top player's goals scored in the season;
- "Top player" refers to the player with the highest number of goals in the season for that team;
- "Top team" refers to the team with the highest combined score of points and player goals.

- "new champions" refers to teams that have achieved a first-place standing in a season and had no previous standing in the same season;
- "experienced coaches" refers to coaches with more than 5 years of coaching experience;
- "English football" refers to football (soccer) leagues in England.

- 'top 3 teams' refers to the teams with the highest average attendance;
- 'drawn the largest crowds' refers to the highest average attendance per game;
- 'grand stadium of time' is a metaphor for the database containing historical data on team performances.
